{"type":"text","timestamp":1775863675339,"sessionID":"ses_286474d8fffeKqLRB2b8M5keEa","part":{"id":"prt_d79b9383b001v5Ejb9thNBU5Uz","messageID":"msg_d79b92f97001sY9bigv574NXuo","sessionID":"ses_286474d8fffeKqLRB2b8M5keEa","type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-023:","time":{"start":1775863675338,"end":1775863675338}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863723659,"sessionID":"ses_286474d8fffeKqLRB2b8M5keEa","part":{"id":"prt_d79b939cc001y5MmyFI0RxCztk","messageID":"msg_d79b92f97001sY9bigv574NXuo","sessionID":"ses_286474d8fffeKqLRB2b8M5keEa","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ce4f4e5367de4477b7ebcd2b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that enable users to interact with and monitor published AI agents.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack → build → publish → **invoke** → **status**. The `invoke` and `status` commands are the final two steps, enabling agent interaction and status monitoring.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `invoke` command that:\n1. Loads workspace metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n2. Parses and validates JSON payload\n3. Parses custom HTTP headers\n4. Resolves the agent endpoint from metadata\n5. Sends HTTP POST request to the agent\n6. Displays the response\n\nImplement the `status` command that:\n1. Loads workspace metadata\n2. Checks if agent is published\n3. Queries the target provider for deployment status\n4. Displays status in a Rich Table\n\n### Value\n\n- **Direct Agent Interaction**: POST JSON payloads to invoke agents\n- **Flexible Headers**: Support custom HTTP headers for authentication\n- **Status Monitoring**: Real-time deployment status check\n- **Dual Provider Support**: Works with both AgentCube CRD and K8s deployments\n- **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Invoke command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n| Invoke runtime | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Core invoke logic |\n| Status command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n| Status runtime | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Core status logic |\n| Metadata models | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata |\n| Tests | `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`, `tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Unit tests |\n\n### CLI Interface\n\n#### invoke\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n#### status\n\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### InvokeRuntime API\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: str, payload: str, header_list: Optional[List[str]], provider: str, verbose: bool) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _resolve_endpoint(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: str) -> str: ...\n    async def _invoke_async(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], provider: str) -> Any: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### StatusRuntime API\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: str, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Agent deployment (handled by publish command)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming\n- Long-running agent sessions\n- Interactive agent REPL\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `httpx>=0.24.0` | Async HTTP client for agent invocation |\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | Metadata serialization |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s status queries |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime class designs\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Invoke and status command requirements and scenarios\n- **AR-020 (pack)** — Requires packed workspace with metadata\n- **AR-021 (build)** — Requires built Docker image\n- **AR-022 (publish)** — Requires published agent endpoint\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **End users** — Fourth and fifth CLI commands in agent workflow\n2. **CI/CD pipelines** — Automated testing and deployment verification\n3. **Monitoring systems** — Status polling integration\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Agent not published | High | Clear error message before HTTP request |\n| Invalid JSON payload | High | Validate JSON before sending request |\n| Invalid header format | Medium | Validate format (key:value) before request |\n| Network timeout | Medium | Configurable timeout, clear error message |\n| K8s cluster inaccessible | Medium | Error handling with fallback message |\n| Provider mismatch | Low | Validate provider matches published type |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Direct HTTP Calls (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Use httpx AsyncClient for direct HTTP invocations.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple implementation\n- No additional dependencies\n- Async support for better performance\n- Works with any HTTP endpoint\n\n**Cons**:\n- No built-in retry logic\n- No connection pooling by default\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with spec requirements and existing patterns.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: SDK-Based Invocation (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Use Python SDK (AgentRuntimeClient) for invocations.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Higher-level abstraction\n- Built-in session management\n\n**Cons**:\n- Adds SDK dependency\n- Less flexible for custom headers\n- Endpoint rewriting not supported\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — spec requires direct HTTP with endpoint rewriting.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: InvokeRuntime Core\n- [x] Implement `_resolve_endpoint()` method\n- [x] Implement `_direct_http_invocation()` method\n- [x] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` method\n- [x] Implement `invoke()` method with payload/header parsing\n\n### Phase 2: StatusRuntime Core\n- [x] Implement `_get_k8s_status()` method\n- [x] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status()` method\n- [x] Implement `get_status()` method\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Integration (invoke)\n- [x] Add invoke command to main.py Typer app\n- [x] Implement Rich output for response display\n- [x] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n- [x] Handle invalid JSON payload validation\n- [x] Handle invalid header format validation\n\n### Phase 4: CLI Integration (status)\n- [ ] Add status command to main.py Typer app\n- [ ] Implement Rich Table for status display\n- [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n- [ ] Handle not_published status\n- [ ] Handle error status\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for InvokeRuntime methods\n- [ ] Unit tests for StatusRuntime methods\n- [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n- [ ] Mock HTTP tests for invoke\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AI-001 | Valid workspace, valid JSON payload | Agent invoked successfully, response displayed |\n| AI-002 | Invalid JSON payload | Error message, exit code 1 |\n| AI-003 | Invalid header format (no colon) | Error message, exit code 1 |\n| AI-004 | Valid custom headers | Headers included in request |\n| AI-005 | Agent not published | Error message, exit code 1 |\n| AI-006 | Session ID in metadata | X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added |\n| AI-007 | AgentCube provider endpoint rewriting | URL rewritten to /v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/ |\n| AI-008 | HTTP error response | Error message with status code |\n| AI-009 | Network timeout | Timeout error message |\n\n### Status Command\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AS-001 | Published agent (agentcube) | AgentRuntime status displayed in table |\n| AS-002 | Published agent (k8s) | Deployment status displayed in table |\n| AS-003 | Agent not published | \"not_published\" status, exit code 1 |\n| AS-004 | Error retrieving status | \"error\" status with error message |\n| AS-005 | Custom namespace | Namespace shown in status |\n| AS-006 | AgentRuntime CR has status field | Display phase from status |\n| AS-007 | AgentRuntime CR has no status | Display \"created_no_status\" |\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Invoke Flow\n\n```\ninvoke command\n    │\n    ├─→ Parse CLI options\n    │   ├─→ Validate JSON payload\n    │   └─→ Parse headers (key:value format)\n    │\n    ├─→ Load workspace metadata\n    │   └─→ Check agent_id or agent_endpoint exists\n    │\n    ├─→ Resolve endpoint\n    │   └─→ Use agent_endpoint if available\n    │   └─→ Construct from agent_id + namespace + port otherwise\n    │\n    ├─→ Add session header if session_id exists\n    │   └─→ X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}\n    │\n    ├─→ HTTP POST to endpoint\n    │   └─→ Content-Type: application/json\n    │   └─→ Body: {payload}\n    │\n    └─→ Display response (Rich output)\n```\n\n### Status Flow\n\n```\nstatus command\n    │\n    ├─→ Load workspace metadata\n    │\n    ├─→ Check if published (agent_id or agent_endpoint)\n    │   └─→ If not published: return \"not_published\"\n    │\n    ├─→ Query provider\n    │   ├─→ agentcube: _get_cr_k8s_status()\n    │   │   └─→ Query AgentRuntime CR\n    │   │   └─→ Return status.phase or \"created_no_status\"\n    │   └─→ k8s: _get_k8s_status()\n    │       └─→ Query Deployment status\n    │       └─→ Return pod status\n    │\n    ├─→ Display in Rich Table\n    │   ├─→ Agent Name\n    │   ├─→ Status\n    │   ├─→ Endpoint\n    │   └─→ Namespace\n    │\n    └─→ Exit code 1 if not_published or error\n```\n\n### Endpoint Resolution Logic\n\n```python\ndef _resolve_endpoint(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: str) -> str:\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    \n    # Use explicit endpoint if available\n    if metadata.agent_endpoint:\n        return metadata.agent_endpoint\n    \n    # Construct from agent_id\n    if metadata.agent_id:\n        namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n        return f\"http://{metadata.agent_id}.{namespace}.svc.cluster.local:{metadata.port}\"\n    \n    raise ValueError(\"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\")\n```\n\n### Header Parsing Logic\n\n```python\ndef _parse_headers(self, header_list: Optional[List[str]]) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    if not header_list:\n        return {}\n    \n    headers = {}\n    for header in header_list:\n        if \":\" not in header:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected key:value\")\n        key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n        headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    \n    return headers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| InvokeRuntime Core | 1-2 hours |\n| StatusRuntime Core | 1 hour |\n| CLI Integration (invoke) | 1-2 hours |\n| CLI Integration (status) | 1-2 hours |\n| Testing | 2-3 hours |\n| **Total** | **6-10 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Existing Implementation Status\n\nThe invoke and status commands have partial implementations:\n\n1. **InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`): 234 lines, implements core invoke logic with async HTTP client\n2. **StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`): 143 lines, implements status retrieval for both providers\n\n### Known Issues\n\n1. **invoke_runtime.py line 62**: Bug - `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` assigns `response` only inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError`\n2. **CLI integration**: Commands need to be added to `main.py` with proper Typer bindings\n3. **Status output**: Needs Rich Table implementation in CLI\n4. **Exit codes**: Status should exit with code 1 for not_published/error\n\n### Gaps to Address\n\n1. Fix UnboundLocalError bug in invoke_runtime.py\n2. Add invoke command to main.py Typer app\n3. Add status command to main.py Typer app\n4. Implement Rich Table output for status\n5. Implement proper exit codes for error conditions\n6. Add session header support (X-Agentcube-Session-Id)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775863723595,"end":1775863723655}}}}
